                        </div>
                        <!-- Column 3 Ends -->                                                		                              
                  </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Three Columns Ends -->
            <!-- Banner Start -->
            <div class="page-header dark-bg">
                  <div class="container">
                        <div class="sixteen columns">
                              <div class="center">
                                    <h3>Colour Anodising has responded to the market demand for a high quality Aqua Blast finish. <br><br>
                                    We now have a state-of-the-art Aqua Blasting facility which utilises the latest technology. <br><br>
                                    Advanced process control measures allow us to maintain excellent consistency.</h3>
                              </div>
                        </div>
                  </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Banner Ends -->
            
            <div class="page-contents dark-bg">
                  <div class="container">
                  
                          <!-- One Column Starts -->
                        <div class="sixteen columns medium-t-b-padding">
                        	<h3>COMPARISON OF BLASTING METHODS</h3>
                        	<p>The illustrations below show the different natures of conventional grit and bead blasting compared to Aqua Blasting</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- One Column Ends --> 
                         
                       <!-- Three Columns Starts -->
                        <div class="one-third column medium-t-b-padding">
                              <img src="images/aquablast/pic-1.jpg" class="scale-with-grid image-shadow" alt="" />
                              <p>Bead blasting demonstrates the aggressive abrasion caused by the severe 90&deg; ricochet of the material fired</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="one-third column medium-t-b-padding">
                              <img src="images/aquablast/pic-2.jpg" class="scale-with-grid image-shadow" alt="" />
                              <p>Dry grit blasting also exhibits severe and uneven pitting, caused again by the 90&deg; ricochet of the inconsistent material</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="one-third column medium-t-b-padding">
                              <img src="images/aquablast/pic-3.jpg" class="scale-with-grid image-shadow" alt="" />
                              <p>Aqua Blasting is a gentler method where the media angle is reduced by the cushioning effect of water to produce a lapping effect travelling across the surface, giving an even satin/polished finish</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Three Columns Ends --> 
                        
                          <!-- One Column Starts -->
                        <div class="sixteen columns medium-t-b-padding">
                        	<p>The key to aqua blasting is that the finish is produced through the flow of water borne abrasive, giving a finer finish due to the flushing action of the water. No media is impregnated into the component, nor is there any dust created by the break-up of media, unlike dry blasting where the finish is produced by sheer force of media impact.</p><br>
							<p>Aqua blasting provides the perfect pre-anodising finish to aluminium</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- One Column Ends --> 
                        
                  </div>
            </div>
      </div>
